		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">L. Phillips</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>203 Broome St</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>New York</placeName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Feb 5</date></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>Friday&#44; the 15<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of Shevat</date>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>1863</date>&#44; <placeName>New York</placeName>.</p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p>Peace and goodness forever.  I seek my<lb/> brethren&#44; and with a greeting of peace&#44; I come to<lb/> speak to my friend&#44; <persName>Rabbi Eliezer <sic>Lesser</sic></persName>&#44; editor&#44;<lb/> of the &#8220;Occident&#44;&#8221; to send me one copy&#44; for I<lb/> have heard from my friend <persName>Leffenherz</persName>&#44; who was in<lb/> <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44; that you mention me for good with re&#45;<lb/>gard to the matter about which I argued with<lb/> the Chazan <persName>Isaacs</persName> which you have no doubt<lb/> noticed in The Israelite&#44; and which completely re&#45;<lb/>futed him&#44; because he was acquainted with me<lb/> for twenty&#45;five years.  Why&#44; then&#44; did you not<lb/> ask me&#63;  Why did you do this&#63;  Perhaps I could<lb/> have found a reply of my own&#44; to prove that<lb/> I had done right.  To make it brief&#44; because the<lb/> letter must be on its way&#44; I beg of <persName>Mr. Eliezar<lb/> <sic>Lesser</sic></persName>&#44; to send to me the said copy of the<lb/> Occident to my address&#44; and I shall reim<lb/>burse you.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your servant&#44; ready to<lb/> serve you&#44; with greetings to your wife and<lb/> children from me and my household&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">L. Phillips</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>203 Broome St.</placeName>&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><placeName>New York</placeName></p>
		</body>
